definitions.text: grow and send out branches or branch-like structures
examples: these plants ramify early and get to be very large

definitions.text: divide into two or more branches so as to form a fork
resembling a fork; divided or separated into two branches
examples: the biramous appendages of an arthropod
long branched hairs on its legson which pollen collects
horseradish grown in poor soil may develop prongy roots
